# 01 — BDO Design Principles

**Status:** Draft v1.0

---

# Purpose

Bitcoin Digital Objects (BDOs) are built around a small set of architectural principles.

These principles guide every specification, implementation and application within the BDO ecosystem.

Technology may evolve.

Implementations may differ.

These principles should remain stable.

---

# Principle 1 — Bitcoin is the Foundation

Bitcoin provides the security, consensus and ownership guarantees upon which Bitcoin Digital Objects are built.

BDOs do not replace Bitcoin.

They extend Bitcoin-native ownership to digital objects.

---

# Principle 2 — Ownership Comes Before Experiences

Applications create experiences.

Bitcoin Digital Objects define ownership.

Experiences may change.

Ownership should remain.

---

# Principle 3 — Objects Outlive Applications

Applications are temporary.

Companies are temporary.

Wallets are temporary.

A Bitcoin Digital Object should remain valid regardless of which application originally created or displayed it.

Ownership should survive software.

---

# Principle 4 — Verification Replaces Trust

Trust is a human decision.

Verification is a technical process.

Bitcoin Digital Objects should maximize independent verification while minimizing required trust.

Users should never need to trust a single company in order to verify ownership.

---

# Principle 5 — Identity is Persistent

Every Bitcoin Digital Object has a persistent identity.

Ownership may change.

Capabilities may evolve.

Applications may interpret the object differently.

Its identity remains the same.

---

# Principle 6 — Ownership is Portable

Ownership should never be locked into a single application.

Users should be free to move their Bitcoin Digital Objects across compatible wallets, services and platforms.

Portability is a fundamental property of digital ownership.

---

# Principle 7 — Standards Enable Interoperability

Interoperability is achieved through open standards.

Standards should define compatibility.

Applications should remain free to innovate.

Competition should happen through user experience rather than proprietary ownership models.

---

# Principle 8 — Capabilities Create Experiences

Bitcoin Digital Objects expose capabilities.

Applications interpret those capabilities.

Different applications may create completely different experiences from the same object.

Capabilities belong to the object.

Experiences belong to applications.

---

# Principle 9 — Layers Should Remain Independent

Each architectural layer has a single responsibility.

Bitcoin provides security.

Taproot Assets provide digital asset primitives.

STAS-01 defines interoperability.

Bitcoin Digital Objects define ownership semantics.

Applications create user experiences.

Keeping responsibilities separate allows the ecosystem to evolve without breaking compatibility.

---

# Principle 10 — The Ecosystem Must Remain Open

Bitcoin Digital Objects are an open category.

No company owns the concept.

No implementation defines the category.

Multiple standards may emerge.

Multiple implementations may coexist.

Innovation should be encouraged through openness rather than control.

---

# Summary

The BDO ecosystem is guided by a simple philosophy:

- Build on Bitcoin.
- Keep standards open.
- Separate ownership from experiences.
- Replace trust with verification.
- Preserve identity.
- Enable interoperability.
- Let applications innovate.

---

# Guiding Principle

> Build open ownership.

> Let everyone build the future.